 Agenda
=========

 OLD Guidelines
-------------
1.  Add a Test class.
2.  Write one function per test.
3.  Add a main method (A separate or same class)
4.  Create object of our test class
5.  Call function on test class object.

Problems
---------
1.  Add new test and add a call to it in main.
2.  If one test fails, other tests below it are blocked.
        Reasons:  (EXCEPTIONS) -- Runtime error -- Program Terminates
        A function throws exception (when it finds something unusal)
            - ElementNotFound
            - ArrayListIndexOutOfBounds
3.  Reporting.
4.  Lot of open browsers on our desktop.

TestNG
-------
1.  Add a Test class.
2.  Write one function per test.
3.  Annotate your function with @Test
4.  If we want to mark test failed
        throw new RuntimeException("Reason of failure");
4.  BETTER
    Use assertions rather that throwing our own exception.


TestNG - TestSuite
Tests of one file
Tests from multiple files
Tests from entire package
Tests from entire project

A word about Exceptions in Java


WebDriverWait ---- Timeouts
